# 2. 内見！モアモアハウス候補！

Minori: This day we've been waiting for... It's finally arrived...
Minori: We get to look at prospective properties for the MORE MORE HOUSE!
Rin: <Woohoo! We get to go house hunting♪>
MEIKO: <I'm very much looking forward to seeing what's on the table!>
Len: <That Kawanishi person found the places you'll be going to see today, right?>
Haruka: That's right. Some are newer than others and they're all by different stations, but they all have the things we need.
Airi: Plus, they're all within budget. If we do happen to find the right one, then it'd be great to close the deal.
Miku: <Umm... I have a question.>
Minori: Ask away, Miku.
Miku: <So, we all decided to tag along since house hunting sounded like a lot of fun...>
Miku: <But are you sure we won't be getting in the way? You're essentially choosing the office for your business...>
Airi: You're all more than welcome to be here!
Haruka: She's right. Once the MORE MORE HOUSE is up and established, we'll get to spend more time with all of you. So, you should all be here for this.
Miku: <Oh, then... Thank you!>
Miku: <Then, we'll help you inspect each one. We've also become quite good at hiding since you've been nice enough to take us to all those different places.>
Kawanishi: Ah, you're already here.
Kawanishi: Oh, I'm sorry. Were you having a call? I can wait until you're finished...
Airi: No, that's okay! We actually just finished.
Kawanishi: I see. Then, shall we? Please join me in the car if you're ready to depart.
Miku: <Yikes... That was a close one...>
Luka: <Overconfidence can lead to mistakes, so we need to be as careful as ever.>
Kawanishi: Alright, that was the last one on the list.
Kawanishi: It's unfortunate that none seemed to fit the bill...
Shizuku: I didn't realize choosing a house would be so difficult.
Haruka: They all seemed really nice on paper.
Airi: Yeah, but the first one we visited had a huge pillar running through the middle, which would've made streaming a bit of a challenge...
Airi: The second one was ninety years old, but the pictures and floor plan made it seem like the perfect choice...
Shizuku: But the real thing told a different story.
Shizuku: That one room in particular... I became so worried that one of us would fall through the floor during dance practice.
Kawanishi: I'm so sorry... I was sure it was a good candidate based on the photos that came attached...
Haruka: No, we also felt the same way... It just goes to show how important it is to actually see the real thing for ourselves.
Minori: But the third one seemed really nice! It was clean and had the perfect floor plan for us!
Airi: Yeah, except for that giant hill we'd have to climb every time. That's on top of it being pretty far from the station, so I really don't think it's worth the trouble.
Haruka: It'd make for a great workout... But we might regret it when it rains or after a long day at work.
Shizuku: Which would defeat the purpose of it being the MORE MORE HOUSE...
Minori: *Sob* No... If it weren't for that hill...!
Kawanishi: I know how you feel... Very few places are both that nice and reasonably priced. But there's always a catch. In this case, a large hill.
Airi: On second thought, I'm beginning to wonder if we're ever going to find what we want in our price range...
Haruka: We may want to start thinking about increasing our budget. However, that also means us having to work a little harder...
Kawanishi: ...
Kawanishi: There's actually one more place that suits you nicely on paper...
Minori: Wait, there is?!
Kawanishi: Yes, but I didn't bring it up until now because it's a bit... Special...
Shizuku: Special...?
Kawanishi: Still, it may be worth a look... There's still the question of whether the property will interest you or not.
Kawanishi: So, if you'll bear with me for a while longer, I can try asking the landlady to let us visit today. How does that sound?
Airi: Then, okay... We still have some time on our hands, so it'd be nice to shop around a little more.
Minori: Yes, we'd love to go!
Kawanishi: Then, please give me a minute while I try to get a hold of her.
Haruka: What do you think is so special about it...?
MEIKO: <What if it's haunted?>
Rin: <Oh! Maybe someone really scary lives right next door!>
Minori: I-I don't know about a haunted house, but I think we can handle having a scary person next door!
Kawanishi: Thank you for your patience! She gave us the green light to visit!
Kawanishi: The group before us just finished, so let's start heading over right now!
Minori: We get to see it?! Thank goodness...!
Airi: Thank you very much. Let's go!
Minori: (Still, why's it so special...?)
Minori: (What kind of house is it...?)
